QUAY SOFTWARE LICENSE AGREEMENT
Version 1.0 - Effective May 26, 2026

Copyright (c) 2026 Drew Chase. All rights reserved.

This License Agreement ("Agreement") governs your use of the Quay desktop
application, command-line interface, and associated libraries (collectively,
the "Software"). By installing, copying, or otherwise using the Software, you
agree to be bound by the terms of this Agreement.


1. DEFINITIONS

   "Free Tier" means the zero-cost edition of the Software limited to one (1)
   workspace, up to fifteen (15) saved connections, and a single integrated
   terminal per connection, with all data stored locally on the machine.

   "Pro Tier" means the paid edition of the Software available at $6 USD per
   month (billed yearly) or $8 USD per month (billed monthly), which includes
   all Free Tier features plus unlimited workspaces and connections, cloud
   sync, SSH tunnels and jump hosts, SFTP over bastion, connection profiles
   with environment variables, multi-tab editor, split panes, find-and-replace
   across files, diff view, file history, multiple terminal tabs, command
   snippets and macros, folder sync rules, scheduled syncs, conflict UI,
   custom themes, tag colors, and keybinding profiles.

   "Team Tier" means the paid edition of the Software available at $12 USD per
   user per month (billed yearly), which includes all Pro Tier features plus
   shared team workspaces with locally-stored credentials, workspace config
   export and import, command history sync across devices and teammates,
   per-server activity logs exportable as JSON, single sign-on (SAML) and SCIM
   provisioning, centralized billing and seat management, and priority support
   with a response time of less than one (1) business day.

   "Lifetime License" means a one-time purchase of $99 USD granting perpetual
   access to all Pro Tier features on up to three (3) personal machines, plus
   one (1) year of cloud sync. Cloud sync may be renewed at $24 USD per year.
   The license itself never expires.

   "Licensee" means you, the individual or entity exercising the rights
   granted under this Agreement.

   "Licensor" means Drew Chase.


