5. CLOUD SYNC AND DATA

   (a) Cloud sync features are available only to Pro Tier, Team Tier, and
       active Lifetime License holders with a current sync subscription.

   (b) The Licensor shall make commercially reasonable efforts to ensure the
       availability and integrity of synced data but shall not be liable for
       data loss arising from service interruptions, account termination, or
       force majeure events.

   (c) The Licensee retains ownership of all data transmitted through or
       stored by the Software. The Licensor shall not access Licensee data
       except as necessary to provide the service or as required by law.


6. TEAM TIER - ADDITIONAL TERMS

   (a) The entity purchasing a Team Tier subscription ("Organization") is
       responsible for managing seats and ensuring compliance with this
       Agreement by all authorized users.

   (b) Team workspaces and shared configurations are owned by the
       Organization. Individual user credentials remain local and are not
       accessible to the Organization or the Licensor.

   (c) Upon termination of a Team Tier subscription, access to shared
       workspaces and cloud-synced team configurations will be revoked.
       Individual users may export their own data prior to termination.


7. LIFETIME LICENSE - ADDITIONAL TERMS

   (a) The Lifetime License grants perpetual access to all features included
       in the Pro Tier as of the date of purchase, plus any future updates to
       the Pro Tier.

   (b) The Lifetime License is valid on up to three (3) machines personally
       owned or operated by the Licensee. The Licensee may deactivate and
       reactivate machines at any time.

   (c) Cloud sync is included for one (1) year from the date of purchase.
       After expiration, the Licensee may renew cloud sync at $24 USD per
       year. All local features remain fully functional without cloud sync.

   (d) The Lifetime License is non-transferable and is bound to the
       purchasing individual. It may not be used for Team Tier features.


8. FREE TIER - ADDITIONAL TERMS

   (a) The Free Tier is provided at no cost and may be used indefinitely
       without registration, subject to the feature limitations defined in
       Section 1.

   (b) The Licensor reserves the right to modify Free Tier feature limits
       with reasonable notice.

   (c) No service-level agreement, cloud sync, or priority support is
       provided with the Free Tier.


9. PAYMENT AND BILLING

   (a) Pro and Team Tier subscriptions are billed in advance on a monthly or
       yearly basis as selected by the Licensee at the time of purchase.

   (b) All fees are non-refundable except as required by applicable law or as
       expressly stated in the Licensor's refund policy.

   (c) The Licensor reserves the right to change pricing with thirty (30)
       days' written notice. Price changes shall not affect the current
       billing cycle.


10. TERMINATION

    (a) The Licensee may terminate this Agreement at any time by uninstalling
        the Software and destroying all copies in the Licensee's possession.

    (b) The Licensor may terminate this Agreement immediately if the Licensee
        breaches any term of this Agreement.

    (c) Upon termination of a paid subscription, the Licensee's access shall
        revert to the Free Tier. No data will be deleted, but features
        exceeding Free Tier limits will become read-only or inaccessible
        until a paid tier is restored.

    (d) Sections 3, 4, 11, 12, and 13 shall survive any termination of this
        Agreement.


